
/*
 * The code snippet demonstrates how to use the [add] slot to append nodes from one location to another. It retrieves nodes from [.arguments] using [get-nodes] and appends them to the [where] node within [data.read]. This allows dynamic modification of the node structure by adding arguments to a specific location. 
 * 
 * 1. [add] - Appends nodes to the specified location.
 * 2. [get-nodes] - Retrieves nodes from [.arguments] to be added.
 */
add:x:./*/data.read/*/where/*
   get-nodes:x:@.arguments/*
